,0.069177,0.055825,0.044466]},{"section":5,"text":"The tender swelling behind the angle of the mandible\u2014so that's the area near the lower jaw, maybe the parotid region or the neck?","dimension":5,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.048472,0.10135,0.11162,0.11236,0.10291,0.09783,0.090849,0.080538,0.085255,0.065107,0.055528,0.048178],"unified_progress":[0.045093,0.083567,0.10292,0.11524,0.11473,0.1039,0.097738,0.087206,0.089281,0.065371,0.051542,0.04341]},{"section":6,"text":"Wait, the angle of the mandible is more towards the lower jaw's back part.","dimension":5,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.045274,0.087593,0.096367,0.10182,0.10066,0.099732,0.095201,0.088297,0.089776,0.075154,0.064914,0.055207],"unified_progress":[0.056562,0.078571,0.094954,0.10669,0.1101,0.10163,0.099126,0.090507,0.087643,0.072293,0.055811,0.046112]},{"section":7,"text":"The swelling there could be a lymph node, but it's tender, so infection is likely.","dimension":5,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.039404,0.084095,0.099765,0.10457,0.10059,0.095454,0.093109,0.086616,0.086693,0.081962,0.067548,0.060196],"unified_progress":[0.046615,0.074801,0.090724,0.10341,0.10539,0.098974,0.098718,0.092673,0.089605,0.081507,0.064847,0.052739]},{"section":8,"text":"The fever adds to that.","dimension":3,"group":8,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.041686,0.087227,0.10675,0.10887,0.10114,0.090127,0.086799,0.081798,0.077143,0.084339,0.068589,0.065537],"unified_progress":[0.042184,0.074603,0.086516,0.097938,0.097892,0.093331,0.096925,0.092834,0.088747,0.09296,0.075777,0.060294]},{"section":9,"text":"Now, the key part is the long-standing ear discharge\u2014six years.","dimension":3,"group":8,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.045839,0.084747,0.093788,0.096016,0.094184,0.091868,0.088463,0.086473,0.08411,0.085068,0.077797,0.071647],"unified_progress":[0.055262,0.074197,0.080604,0.087684,0.090175,0.091689,0.093078,0.093569,0.091147,0.09182,0.082147,0.068629]},{"section":10,"text":"Chronic ear discharge with granulations in the ear canal suggests chronic otitis media.","dimension":5,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.035805,0.077022,0.088153,0.094563,0.096483,0.098569,0.097297,0.09251,0.09417,0.083491,0.075225,0.066711],"unified_progress":[0.049877,0.070008,0.084816,0.095708,0.098486,0.099548,0.097303,0.093988,0.093605,0.083636,0.071903,0.061121]},{"section":11,"text":"Chronic otitis media can lead to complications like mastoiditis, which is an infection of the mastoid bone behind the ear.","dimension":5,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.030389,0.068374,0.082411,0.093493,0.098864,0.1018,0.10222,0.096071,0.095565,0.087274,0.075585,0.067957],"unified_progress":[0.042009,0.063755,0.082854,0.09373,0.099508,0.10655,0.1012,0.096944,0.095031,0.084966,0.072395,0.061059]},{"section":12,"text":"The mastoid process is right there behind the ear, near the angle of the mandible.","dimension":5,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.038899,0.079332,0.088376,0.095364,0.095767,0.098303,0.096703,0.090977,0.097106,0.081607,0.071831,0.065736],"unified_progress":[0.046468,0.071286,0.08974,0.10168,0.10741,0.10338,0.10042,0.093644,0.093585,0.075852,0.062648,0.053887]},{"section":13,"text":"So mastoiditis would cause a tender swelling there.","dimension":5,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.036055,0.075492,0.087903,0.094898,0.095518,0.095484,0.095208,0.090268,0.092525,0.08574,0.075661,0.075249],"unified_progress":[0.03977,0.066224,0.083122,0.094934,0.1,0.099937,0.09874,0.094325,0.093942,0.084546,0.075346,0.069109]},{"section":14,"text":"Torticollis in this context might be due to the swelling and pain from the mastoid infection, causing the child to hold their head tilted to reduce discomfort.","dimension":9,"group":9,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.042562,0.076683,0.0803,0.085796,0.090687,0.094972,0.096935,0.094915,0.092712,0.08735,0.081365,0.075722],"unif